<item>
            <title>[JDK-8302615] make JVMTI thread cpu time functions optional for virtual threads</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8302615</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Make support of two timer functions for virtual threads optional:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;- GetCurrentThreadCpuTime&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;- GetThreadCpuTime&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
To do that we can relax the spec as in patch below:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
diff --git a/src/hotspot/share/prims/jvmti.xml b/src/hotspot/share/prims/jvmti.xml&lt;br/&gt;
index 4baaca503c0..5f68fc9a7a9 100644&lt;br/&gt;
--- a/src/hotspot/share/prims/jvmti.xml&lt;br/&gt;
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/prims/jvmti.xml&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -11058,7 +11058,8 @@ myInit() {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;/parameters&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;errors&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;error id=&amp;quot;JVMTI_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_OPERATION&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
-          Current thread is a virtual thread.&lt;br/&gt;
+          The current thread is a virtual thread and the implementation does not support&lt;br/&gt;
+          getting the current thread CPU time when the current thread is a virtual thread.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;/error&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;/errors&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;/function&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -11140,7 +11141,8 @@ myInit() {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;/parameters&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;errors&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;error id=&amp;quot;JVMTI_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_OPERATION&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
-          &amp;lt;paramlink id=&amp;quot;thread&amp;quot;/&amp;gt; is a virtual thread.&lt;br/&gt;
+          &amp;lt;paramlink id=&amp;quot;thread&amp;quot;/&amp;gt; is a virtual thread and the implementation does not&lt;br/&gt;
+          support getting the thread CPU time of a virtual thread.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;/error&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;/errors&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;/function&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
